      <h1 class="page-title" property="headline">Automated Testing</h1>
    </header>
    <div property="text" class="entry-content">
      <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>

<p>An important part of the API life cycle is to make sure that what the contract says is what is actually implemented, and that&#x2019;s the place for Automated Testing. Testing works by taking your API Description, creating expectations based on the requests and responses in the blueprint, making requests to your API, and seeing if the responses match. The goal is to have the documentation and implementation of the API in sync&#x2014;no more outdated API documentation.</p>

<h2 id="topics">Topics</h2>

